-- Russia Caps Retail Fuel Prices Until Election, Kommersant Says
-- B y   J a k e   R u d n i t s k y
-- 2012-01-23T05:22:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-23/russia-caps-retail-fuel-prices-until-election-kommersant-says.html
Russia oil producers agreed to
freeze retail prices for motor fuels at December levels until
the March presidential election, Kommersant reported, citing
unidentified company officials.  Deputy Prime Minister  Igor Sechin  ordered the companies to
cap prices at a Jan. 10 meeting and promised unspecified
compensation for any losses that result from the price ceiling,
the Moscow-based newspaper said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jake Rudnitsky in Moscow at 
 jrudnitsky@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
